                    <span>Hi!</span> I am Divyaksh Shukla, a PhD student at IIT-Kanpur
                    in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering, joined
                    July 2023. Before pursuing my doctoral studies I was a Senior
                    Software Engineer at Itron. Itron is a US-based company working
                    on smart utility metering. I worked on electrical load forecasting,
                    where I developed end-to-end solutions for clients to see forecasting
                    results on a web-based dashboard.<br /><br />

                    I did my M.Tech from BITS-Pilani in the field of Data
                    Science and Engineering. I wrote my thesis under the
                    guidance of Dr. Frank Monforte, Director Itron, titled
                    "AI-Based Electrical Load forecasting using real-time load
                    data in the presence of volatile behind-the-meter Solar PV
                    power generation".<br /><br />

                    I intend to bring the disparate worlds of Machine Learning
                    and Operations together, popularly called MLOps. With my
                    industrial experience and knowledge in Continuous
                    Integration and Deployment systems using Azure Cloud,
                    Kubernetes and Docker, I wish to make a seamless environment
                    to build-improve-deploy models for real-world operations.
